    {
      "_id": "I3ghe95n7HWlMhrE",
      "name": "Autodestruct system",
      "type": "starshipOtherSystem",
      "img": "systems/sfrpg/icons/default/gears.svg",
      "system": {
        "cost": 1,
        "costMultipliedBySize": true,
        "description": {
          "chat": "",
          "gmnotes": "",
          "short": "",
          "unidentified": "",
          "value": "<p>An autodestruct system is a self-destruct mechanism that removes the crew’s ability to avoid destruction in a crisis. When a starship outfitted with an autodestruct system is reduced to 0 Hull Points, the autodestruct system activates, destroying the ship it’s built into. Starships in hexes adjacent to a starship as it autodestructs take damage to the appropriate quadrants equal to half the destroyed starship’s maximum Hull Points, mitigated by shields as normal.</p>\n<p>An autodestruct system is hardwired into the ship and has no interface that can be hacked or disabled. Once installed, it can be removed only with 1 day of work and a successful Engineering check (DC = 15 + 1-1/2 Ã— the starship’s tier). Failing this check means the autodestruct system remains active, and the engineer is aware of that fact.</p>"
        },
        "isPowered": true,
        "modifiers": [],
        "pcu": 0,
        "slug": "",
        "source": "SOM pg. 27"
      }
    },
    {
      "_id": "H51OZvqsLzkEKAiz",
      "name": "Biometric locks",
      "type": "starshipSecuritySystem",
      "img": "systems/sfrpg/icons/default/cctv-camera.svg",
      "system": {
        "cost": 5,
        "costMultipliedBySize": false,
        "description": {
          "chat": "",
          "gmnotes": "",
          "short": "",
          "unidentified": "",
          "value": "<p>The systems of a starship with biometric locks can only be used by certain creatures, designated when the locks are installed; this list can be updated by any creature who can gain access to the ship’s computer systems. A successful Computers check (DC = 20 + 1-1/2 Ã— the tier of the starship) can bypass these locks.</p>"
        },
        "isPowered": false,
        "modifiers": [],
        "pcu": null,
        "slug": "",
        "source": "CRB pg. 300"
      }
    },
    {
      "_id": "Rnib8DDAtb0DiTBl",
      "name": "Common crew quarters",
      "type": "starshipCrewQuarter",
      "img": "systems/sfrpg/icons/default/bunk-beds.svg",
      "system": {
        "cost": null,
        "costMultipliedBySize": false,
        "description": {
          "chat": "",
          "gmnotes": "",
          "short": "",
          "unidentified": "",
          "value": "<p>Common crew quarters are the most basic type. They consist of simple bunks (sometimes folding out from the side of a hallway) or other similarly austere places to rest. Crew members who sleep in common quarters usually keep their personal possessions in a footlocker. Common crew quarters also include a communal bathroom (which includes a military-style shower) and a tiny galley (big enough to prepare only the most basic of meals). Starships with crews numbering in the dozens or hundreds often have massive barracks where crew members sleep in shifts .</p>"
        },
        "modifiers": [],
        "slug": "",
        "source": "CRB pg. 298"
      }
    },
